==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Isolate
<hw>I"so*late</hw> <pr>(⟦imac⟧"s⟦osl⟧*l⟦amac⟧t <it>or</it>
⟦imac⟧s"⟦osl⟧*l⟦amac⟧t; 277)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Isolated</conjf>
<pr>(⟦imac⟧"s⟦osl⟧*l⟦amac⟧`t⟦ecr⟧d)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Isolating</conjf>
<pr>(⟦imac⟧"s⟦osl⟧*l⟦amac⟧`t⟦icr⟧ng)</pr>.]</vmorph> <ety>[It.
<ets>isolato</ets>, p. p. of <ets>isolare</ets> to isolate, fr.
<ets>isola</ets> island, L. <ets>insula</ets>. See 2d <er>Isle</er>, and
cf. <er>Insulate</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>To place in a detached situation; to place by itself
or alone; to insulate; to separate from others; <as>as, to
<ex>isolate</ex> an infected person from others; to <ex>isolate</ex> the
troublemakers in a classroom</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><q>Short <qex>isolated</qex> sentences were the mode in which ancient
wisdom delighted to convey its precepts.</q> <rj><qau>Bp.
Warburton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Elec.)</fld> <def>To insulate. See
<er>Insulate</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>To separate (a substance) from
all foreign substances; to make pure; to obtain in a free state; <as>as,
to <ex>isolate</ex> the desired product from a reaction
mixture</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <fld>(Microbiol.)</fld> <def>To obtain a culture of a
microorganism in pure form (from a complex mixture); <as>as, to
<ex>isolate</ex> <spn>Eschericia coli</spn> from a patient's
blood</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Isolate</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Isolate
<hw>I"so*late</hw> <pr>(⟦imac⟧"s⟦osl⟧*l⟦asl⟧t <it>or</it>
⟦imac⟧s"⟦osl⟧*l⟦amac⟧t`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Something that has
been isolated; <as>as, an <ex>isolate</ex> of a powerful antibiotic from
a tropical plant; an <ex>isolate</ex> of tuberculosis bacillus from an
infected patient</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Isolated</ent>⟦br⟧
